casebody.data:
Friday, October 30, 1992

MISCELLANEOUS DISMISSALS

92-840. Farley v. Licking Cty. Court of Common Pleas, Domestic Relations Div.

In Prohibition. This cause originated in this court on the filing of a complaint for a writ of prohibition. Upon consideration of relator’s application to dismiss,

IT IS ORDERED by the court that said application be, and the same is hereby, granted, effective October 29, 1992.

ACCORDINGLY, IT IS FURTHER ORDERED by the court that this cause be, and hereby is, dismissed.
